Here we add the support for simple memory management. Basically we define
two kernel apis:

	get_free_page
	free_page

to allocate and deallocate phisical memory pages.
This is the map of our memory:

    ------------
   |////////////|
   |____________|
   |            | 0x01000 Start Kernel 
   |            |
   |   Kernel   |
   |            |
   |            |
   |            |
   |____________| KEND (we defined an arbitrary upper limit for kernel mm)
   |  page 0    | Start Memory for processes
   |____________|
   |  page 1    |
   |____________|
   |            | we reserved 63 pages for processes memory
   |            | (63 is an arbitrary e temporarly value)
   |   ......   |
   |____________|
   | page 63    |
   |____________|

